<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=8321&amp;p=35532#p35532"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Googleized Opaque [7 style]]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=8321&amp;p=35532#p35532"><![CDATA[
Googleized Opaque [7 style] for CSM 4.3.0<br /><br />I borrowed the buttons, etc from the screenshot of Google image search.<br />It's kind of dark. Might not be useful on some LCD displays, <br />especially if the taskbar is at the top. The selector button could be difficult to see. <br />I made the hover text color white to help discern.<br />There are no white submenus in this skin. They are banned. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /><br /><br /><br />EDIT: Ok, now it's revB. <br /><br />Most horizontal separators can butt up against the vertical line.<br /><br /><br />This is the only way that I know of by extending the separators further than the bitmaps padding. <br />Maybe some simply worded text and - number? I bet Ivo knows.<br />There had to be some compromises along the way, to achieve that look, as it's a sneaky way to do it. <br />Like the small offset search box button, vertically offset arrows and spaces in between 1st column entries.<br />The submenu offset(part of the submenu that lays on top of selector button), is chaotic, because of too many variables going on. <br /><br />The option can be selectively turned off.<br /><br />I thought adding all the extra button images with extra invisible padding, would increase the file size a lot. Nope.<br />Due to no texture, and using good old png, skin file size is 90 KB.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Tue Mar 06, 2018 2:04 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
